          version="5.0-subset Scilab"
          xml:id="XcosMenuRegionToSuper">
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>Region_to_Super_Block</refname>
    <refpurpose>Menu: Form a Super Block with a part of the current diagram.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      To form a Super Block with a part of the current diagram it is
      possible to follow to different ways:
    </para>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>.</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
	    First <link linkend="XcosSelect">select</link> the
          desired blocks (the internal links will be automatically
          added) then activate the
          <literal>Region to Super Block</literal> menu.
	  </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term>.</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
	    First activate the <literal>Region to Super
	    Block</literal> menu, then select a rectangular area
	    around the desired blocks (press left on a point which is
	    not over an object to select the corner of the rectangle
	    then drag the mouse to make the rectangle include all the
	    desired objects and release the mouse button).
	    </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
      <para>
      Selected region is replaced by a <link linkend="SUPER_f">Super
      Block</link> and links are redrawn.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>See Also</title>
    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member> <link linkend="SUPER_f">Super Block</link> </member>
      <member> <link linkend="XcosMenuCreateMask">Create Mask</link> </member>
     </simplelist>
   </refsection>
</refentry>
